    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-27T15:39:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-12-27T15:39:00-05:00" n="380"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d380">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">886A.2553/12–2754: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 380<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Saudi Arabia</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d380fn1">Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_BF1"
                            >Boardman</persName> and cleared by <gloss target="#t_NE1">NE</gloss> in
                        draft.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-12-27T15:39:00-05:00"
                            >December 27, 1954—3:39 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>280. For your information <persName corresp="#p_DJT1">Duce</persName>
                    <gloss target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> told Department today that Board
                    Directors met New York December 22 and decided as compromise measure to deal
                    with Onassis problem it may offer place some <gloss target="#t_Aramco1"
                        >Aramco</gloss> tankers under Saudi flag provided that (1) <gloss
                        target="#t_SAG1">SAG</gloss> enacts suitable shipping laws and (2) Article 4
                    of Onassis Agreement concerning preferences be eliminated. <gloss
                        target="#t_Aramco1">Aramco</gloss> querying field for comment. <persName
                        corresp="#p_DJT1">Duce</persName> emphasized decision not final and that
                    some Directors still have considerable misgivings this undertaking.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF2">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
